##That's what you need to know to get on a plane at rush hour

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

Air Circulation is not the main problem

During the SARS epidemic in 2003, passengers on 35 flights around the world were suspected to have been infected by fellow passengers with SARS, but only four flights were confirmed with suspected cases, 16 people in all. At the 56th World Health Assembly in 2003, the WHO's head of infectious diseases, David Heyman, stressed that these infections occurred before airlines imposed stringent health screening measures on boarding passengers.

Compared with the environment of the train, the plane is small and airtight, but its interior has a complex and special air circulation system. In general, on an aircraft, air is sucked out from the bottom, pressurized and filtered into the air conditioning system, where it is filtered through the HEPA system, Chen Jianguo, a captain of aircraft such as the Boeing 737, told scidev.net. Filtered air through the main pipe, like irrigation, along the cabin roof, every 3 ~ 4 rows or 4 ~ 5 rows of export discharge, the overall "Feng" type. This air system design, so that a few rows between the formation of a more independent micro-circulation system, to avoid the cross-flow of air in the cabin.

Image | shutterstock

According to an article published by the Civil Aviation Administration in the 7th issue of International Aviation magazine in 2013, "the air quality in the passenger cabin is comparable to that in the operating room -- Florida -- why the chances of contracting SARS by air travel are low, " HEPA air filtration can remove more than 99.97% of particles with diameter of 0.003 Micron. The average diameter of the new coronavirus (2019-nCov) is about 0.1 Î¼m. Single virus, adsorbed in dust and other particles on the virus group, flying foam, these forms are in the role of HEPA gas filter.

On February 2, the Civil Aviation Administration issued a notice on the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia during the Chinese New Year Return Journey, which seeks to minimize the spread of the disease by aircraft, one of them is to use the maximum amount of air in the aircraft. In the past, the air on an airplane was completely changed every three to five minutes. During the outbreak, the General Administration of Civil Aviation Requirements is to open the maximum ventilation, 2-3 minutes for a change. This speeds up the vertical flow of air in the cabin, making the human body hobble air stay shorter.

In addition to increasing the frequency of air changes, some airlines have also replaced air filters in their aircraft air recycling systems to provide cleaner air. Aircraft and air recirculation systems from different manufacturers have different cleaning standards, Chen Jianguo told the economist, citing the 750 hour and 7500 hour recirculation categories of air filters, the corresponding daily replacement frequency is about every two months and every two years. "It's the same as if you buy your own air purifier and change it every 30 days, but every 90 days, and you end up with clean air that meets standards, " Chen Jianguo said

Special Times, special measures

In addition to increasing the amount of air flow in the aircraft, in the notice on the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia during the return journey during the Spring Festival, the Civil Aviation Administration also proposed measures such as increasing disinfection frequency, adjusting service flow during flight, urging passengers to wear face masks, and temperature measurement at the boarding gate.

In a written interview, the relevant person in charge of China Eastern Airlines told this newspaper, at present, China Eastern Airlines all aircraft are strict after the implementation of disinfection. For the aircraft carrying out flights, China Eastern Airlines requires the aircraft on the ground over the station, short stops, must use "1452 aircraft cabin cleaning disinfectant" , the cabin daily need to clean the parts of the spray, wipe processing. For post-flight cleaning and deep cleaning, further in-depth disinfection is also required.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Expedition photography

On the ground, China Eastern's ferries, passenger elevators and other vehicles are required to be disinfected every 4 hours, and once a suspected case, immediately after the use of vehicles for disinfection. The seats, armrests, doors and railings, handrails and pedals of the ferries will also be key disinfected. After the vehicles are used and disinfected, they will be parked in the designated area, and the doors and windows will be opened to maintain ventilation. All bags must be sealed, disinfected, and then put into a special recycling Bin, designated by the designated car to the airport designated location for parking, to be treated by professional medical waste treatment institutions. After the garbage disposal, also want to carry on the strict disinfection by special person. The machine sewage into the sewage tank, the same must be in proportion to the concentration of disinfectants or disinfectant tablets, bleach disinfection, disinfection time of 2 hours after discharge.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tian Jianqing, deputy director of the Medical Emergency Center at Wuhan Tianhe Airport, told This newspaper that after passengers board the plane, when they arrive at their destinations or when they are not eating, they may be sprayed with aerosol disinfectant, depending on the level of risk of infection. This kind of disinfectant is harmless to human body, but has certain killing effect to the germ, may play the role of reducing the possibility of infection to a certain extent.

As far as we know, close contacts in close proximity to the patient are highly contagious. Tian Jianqing told our reporter that the aircraft's air microcirculation system makes the 3-5 rows a relatively independent area, but that doesn't mean that if there are patients on the plane, the only people who were in close contact with him were three rows in front of him and three rows behind him, one aisle away from the wide-body plane. Crew members who work closely with patients, as well as passengers who use the same bathroom as patients, may be at risk of transmission. While the patient may be moving around in the cabin, all crew members will be considered close contacts.

In order to avoid possible spread of the virus on the flight, China Eastern Airlines said that all flight personnel must wear masks and other protective equipment before taking up positions. The airline's lounge and on-board services have also been fully adjusted, strictly control and simplify the non-essential machine supplies, eliminate the possible transmission contact.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some domestic airlines have canceled the issuance of blankets and other items on domestic routes, replacing hot meals with packaged foods and reducing the frequency of on-board services.

If a suspected case is found on board, the crew will take special measures. Tian Jianqing said, flight attendants usually do this:"1. Put on or put on a mask to dissuade the suspect from voluntary activities. 2. Adjust your seat if you have a spare seat in the cabin, move it to the back of the plane if necessary, and separate it from other passengers. 3. Provide masks for other passengers who do not have masks and guide other passengers to use other toilets, etc. ."

Guide to epidemic prevention for ordinary passengers

In addition, ordinary passengers can also use what epidemic prevention measures? Tian Jianqing offers the following advice:

Sanlian Life Weekly: During the flight passengers and crew are wearing masks, in addition to what we should pay attention to?

Tian Jianqing: Wearing a mask can indeed greatly reduce the possibility of transmission of droplets. However, in the dining, washing face and other time is necessary to take off the mask, this time there is a certain risk of infection.

In order to avoid the risk of infection if you take off your face mask during meals, we recommend that airlines introduce seat spacing and separate meal times into their in-flight meals. When the passenger washes the face, must first wash the hand according to the standard to surpass 20 seconds, the self-pays attention to the toilet clean.

Sanlian Life Weekly: Is it necessary for passengers to avoid eating and going to the toilet on the plane?

Tian Jianqing: On Short flights, you can really reduce your exposure by eating before and after the flight. Long-distance cross-ocean flight, do not advocate starving in flight, should be in accordance with the crew arrangement to implement separate meals, that is, to reduce exposure, but also to avoid starving in the body.

In addition, patients with diseases such as hypoglycemia and insulin imbalance in diabetes should be informed of their condition to the crew according to the needs of the disease treatment, ensure timely meals, and scientific and timely medication according to the advice of the clinician.

Tri-union Life Weekly: Is there any risk of infection from contact with luggage or cargo?

Tian Jianqing: It has been reported that viral nucleic acids have been detected on the doorknobs that the patient came into contact with, and COVID-19 pneumonia has been confirmed as a contact infection. However, academician Li Lanjuan said, as long as the regular hand-washing and standard hand-washing, it can avoid not wearing gloves and lead to general contact with infectious goods. As a result, we don't have to panic too much about touching things and checking luggage.

Should people with weakened immune systems be advised to use less public transport?

Tian Jianqing: In the case of rampant infectious diseases, the weak and sickly, low resistance of the population, it is indeed more should reduce travel.

LIVESCIENCE: What medical assistance should you seek if you feel unwell during the flight?

Tian Jianqing: Sick passengers should read the airline's statement carefully before buying tickets, and should decide whether to travel by air based on the advice of a clinical doctor in case of ill health. Some Airlines also require elderly and seriously ill, unaccompanied and disabled students to provide health reports or recent medical records or medical advice from doctors before they can be shipped.

In addition, the disease is dynamic and can be assessed at the time of discharge and can travel by plane, but can still cause poor health at the time of boarding due to late nights, baggage handling, catching a flight, not taking medication on time and on schedule, etc. , there is a possibility that air travel may be denied by temporary reduction of cabin capacity. If this occurs, the sick should be accepted and understood, because life and health are the most precious.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A still from "inner beauty. "

Therefore, should try to avoid traveling alone with illness, should be familiar with their own illness and treatment of relatives and friends traveling by air. Before boarding, you should get enough sleep, maintain your energy, and minimize unnecessary physical exertion, such as long-distance carry-on bags that far exceed your hand luggage allowance. Remember to take medicine on time and essential emergency medicine with you at all times, and take medicine on time during the flight. If you feel unwell on the way, you should seek help from the attendant in time and indicate your condition. If necessary, the crew will take appropriate measures to give assistance.

Tri-union Life Weekly: In the absence of conditions for effective isolation, if suspected cases are found, how should neighboring passengers protect themselves?

Tian Jianqing: passengers should wear a mask when they find someone around them with fever, cough or other respiratory system symptoms. If they don't have a mask, they can use their arms to cover up their face, or turn their head while standing up their collar and wearing a hat, to prevent the spread of flying droplets; to give a mask when there is excess mask, so that they can wear a preliminary isolation; when there is no excess mask, you can turn your head and whisper to persuade them to temporarily cover their mouth and nose with an arm or a tissue; to report the situation to the crew; In the aircraft is not bumpy circumstances can go to other positions to extend the distance.

If a suspected case is found on a flight, how long will the fellow passengers be followed?

Tian Jianqing: It is to press disease incubation time commonly, from the moment that separates with suspect patient, it is 14 days commonly.
